for the yi action camera (小蚁运动相机),
which is unfortunately out of support,
the website is still up, but the company seems dead,
the official android app won't install on recent android.

this script simply starts the live stream, no other features are planned at this point.

usage:
deno run --allow-net=192.168.42.1:7878 yi.ts

it needs to keep running to keep the control connection alive.
^c to stop it when you're done.

then play rtsp://192.168.42.1/live

note:
thanks to termux, we can run this on an android phone
mpv needs --rtsp-transport=udp, or =lavf, otherwise it defaults to tcp

ref: https://github.com/deltaflyer4747/Xiaomi_Yi/blob/master/Standalone_scripts/Camera_video_stream.py
